    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect byte ordering in NFAPI packing/unpacking functions\n\n### Summary\nThe NFAPI library had incorrect byte ordering implementations in all push/pull functions. The big-endian and little-endian cases were swapped, causing data to be packed/unpacked with wrong byte order. This affected functions downstream of `pack_nmm_frequency_bands_value` and other NFAPI message handling.\n\nThe issue manifested as incorrect frequency band values being exchanged between VNF and PNF, causing configuration failures during cell setup.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c`: Fixed byte ordering in push16, pushs16, push32, pushs32, pull16, pulls16, pull32, pulls32 functions.\n\nTo reproduce: Configure a PNF with specific frequency bands and observe that the bands reported back from the PNF don't match the configured values. Tracing the NFAPI messages will show byte-swapped values in the band list TLVs.\n"
}